This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation in histopathology images. It also involves the use of fully convolutional networks (FCNs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves the development of a new weakly supervised learning algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The use of constraints to assist the learning process suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper involves the analysis of large-scale histopathology image data sets, which suggests that it could belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper mentions that the proposed algorithm can be applied to various applications in medical imaging beyond histopathology images, such as MRI, CT, and ultrasound images, which suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
